This paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of information-theoretic regularizers to encourage agents to reveal or hide their intentions, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents results on asymmetric information games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
